<hl>
<seg id=1> Foreign cooperation in Chinese building materials industry developed quickly. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, 19 March, by Li Jianmin Strengthening foreign cooperation in Chinese building materials industry was considered as the major measures of development. The domain of foreign capital expended rapidly, and at present, the total foreign capital of the industry was US$5 billion. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> An official of the National Bureau of Building materials told a reporter today that making use of the loans from the World Bank and the Asian Bank, a larger number of cement projects in Tongling, Anhui and Xiangxiang, Hunan had been put into operation. </seg>
<seg id=4> The domain of foreign investment made further development in the areas of new building materials, high technology and processing industry of building materials. </seg>
<seg id=5> Making use of US$100 million export loan on a favorable terms from Italy, the transformation projects of high sanitary ceramics made progress in Shanxi, Shandong, Guangdong, Jilin, Hunan, etc. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Recently, the Chinese building materials industry signed bilateral agreements with the governments and transnational corporations of Holland, Germany, Thailand, Greece, Australia, Japan, France, Denmark, etc., which improved the foreign partnership. </seg>
<seg id=7> Last year, the total export benefit of the Chinese building materials industry exceeded US$2,100 million. The cement export was 12 million tons, 46% over the year before, and it was an all-time high. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> Besides, in recent years, China introduced the assembly line of predecomposition kiln and built large cement enterprises in Yidong, Ningguo, Huaihai, Liuzhou, etc. The annual production capacity was 2.2 million tons of cement increase. </seg>
</p>
